  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "AI enhances resilience in agriculture and food systems through predictive analytics for crop yield, early pest detection, and real-time climate-smart decision-making.",
    "These tools enable proactive adaptation, reduce crop losses, and optimize irrigation and supply chains, increasing robustness against droughts, pests, and supply shocks.",
    "The 21st century is often called the \"century of the city\" because more than half of the global population resides in urban areas (Amen, 2024), making these hubs critical for determining our resilience.",
    "However, cities face escalating threats from floods, hurricanes, wildfires, and other extreme weather events intensified by climate change (Wang J. et al., 2024).",
    "Climate change exacerbates urban flooding, leading to overwhelmed drainage systems and extensive infrastructure damage (Lu et al., 2023)."
  ],
